The time has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a bit of decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and hearth. Coffering the chimney, replacing the damaged plaster and sanding. Make a custom-made wardrobe.
We always start with a quick sketch with a pencil...
The messy stage is over.
I found several dead birds at the back of the conduit; all dried out :(
Ready for the plasterer next week
Ravi to see the little niche on the side
Insert the new closet here (not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look at what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought to add a charming little ventilation opening to prevent the chimney from getting humidity
The roofer took care of installing the hat and the awning. It should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer is finished. We'll install the floor tomorrow!
The underlayment of wood shavings is laid, I improvised an extractor of wood shavings with a toilet paper roll as an accessory for the vacuum cleaner 😂
A part of the boards is sorted and ready to be placed. We're just taking a tea break
Well, the progress was slow today due to extremely delicate cuts around the door posts to get a smooth transition to the hallway (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com cursed me out
Finished, but on the door hinges! The icing on the cake: the unquenchable instructions to assemble the new bed. We're going to sleep well tonight!
Still to be done: the hallway floor, all the skirting boards. The interior designer comes in a month, so until then, at home, it's the chic of unrendered plaster
Short evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door posts using a tenon saw/a chisel at the spot where we want the floor to be perfectly adjusted.
The underlayment of the hallway, made of foam board, is also laid down
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then departure at 5 a.m. this morning to go pick up Thing 1 at Heathrow, followed by a nap and the final stretch for the hallway; skirting boards installed. We'll take care of the sealing when the adhesive has dried.
